findings.recommendation:
Add a companion test (or replace this one) that patches subprocess.run to raise subprocess.TimeoutExpired or OSError on the 'show rule name=all' call — do NOT mock _list_firewall_rules_by_prefix itself. Then call remove_firewall_rules() and assert (a) it does not raise, (b) delete calls are made for the fixed-list fallback. Example:

  @patch('src.system_config.sys.platform', 'win32')
  @patch('src.system_config.subprocess.run')
  def test_remove_by_prefix_fallback_on_subprocess_exception(self, mock_run):
      mock_run.side_effect = [subprocess.TimeoutExpired('netsh', 30), MagicMock(), ...]
      remove_firewall_rules()
      delete_calls = [c for c in mock_run.call_args_list if 'delete' in str(c)]
      assert len(delete_calls) == len(BROWSER_EXES) * len(STUN_PORTS)
